In mathematics, the '''Young–Deruyts development''' is a method of writing [[Invariant (mathematics)|invariants]] of an [[Group action (mathematics)|action of a group]] on an ''n''-dimensional [[vector space]] ''V''
in terms of invariants depending on at most ''n''–1 vectors {{harvs|last=Dieudonné|last2=Carrell|year1=1970|year2=1971|loc2=p.36, 39}}..

